                <note rend="inline" type="source">841D.01/292: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-04T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 4, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. Below is the text of a further note which we propose to send to Prime
                    Minister de Valera. Although the draft had been prepared before the receipt of
                    your telegram no. 59, March 21,<note n="38" xml:id="d170fn38">Not
                        printed.</note> we have added to it certain suggestions from your telegram.
                    Please telegraph any comments you have on this note. This draft is being
                    telegraphed to Winant today for clearance with the British. As soon as the
                    British approval is received we shall telegraph you. We believe it would be
                    better for you to send the note rather than to deliver it in person. We plan to
                    give this note to the press as soon as you telegraph that it has been delivered.
                    The text of the note follows as Department No. 57.<note n="39" xml:id="d170fn39"
                        >See footnote 40, <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
